divs: Sighting DetailsI WAS OUT IN FRONT OF OUR HOUSE LOOKING UP AT THE NIGHT SKY. WE LIVE OUT IN THECOUNTRY SO WE HAVE A CLEAR VIEW OF THE SKY. AN OBJECT THAT APPEARED TO DISKSHAPED OR OVAL PASSED OVERHEAD. IT WAS VERY HIGH IN THE SKY. THERE DIDNTAPPEAR TO BE ANY LIGHTS ON THE OBJECT. THE OBJECT WAS ILLUMINATED FOR A SHORTTIME BY THE SETTING SUN. IT HAD A SIMILAR APPEARANCE TO A SATELLITE PASSING BY,BUT IT MOVED AT A SPEED FASTER THAN AN AIRPLANE OR SATELLITE AND A BIT SLOWERTHAN A METEOR. I THOUGHT IT MIGHT BE A METEOR AT FIRST BUT THIS OBJECT WASSMOOTH AND REFLECTIVE. IT APPEARED TOO LOW TO BE A METEOR. THE OBJECT ITSELFWAS MOVING AT A HIGH RATE OF SPEED FROM SOUTH TO NORTH.
